A vintage 1950s advertising illustration style image showing a stern corporate executive in a gray flannel suit standing before a massive, impossibly tangled wall of brass nameplates, each engraved with absurdly long abbreviated codes. The executive holds a large pair of golden scissors, having just snipped through several plates which fall away to reveal simple, elegant single-word plaques beneath. The color palette features muted teals, warm creams, and pops of red. The scene has the optimistic, slightly exaggerated aesthetic of mid-century magazine advertisements, with bold shadows and a sense of triumphant simplification emerging from bureaucratic chaos.
